{"article_id":"uB8scpL954fNCVtR","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"As someone","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"who works full-time on healing the angry tone of our public discourse and polarization","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that divides our nation ,","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"the Kavanaugh hearings and searing debates","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"that followed","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"were difficult to watch .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"The depth of hate and personal vilification","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"expressed by both sides","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"was overwhelming .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"An hour after Senator Susan Collins","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"Susan Margaret CollinsRepublicans show signs of discomfort in defense of Trump","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"Embracing President Mike Pence might be GOP 's best play","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"GOP battens down the hatches after release of Trump whistleblower complaint MORE","depth":12},{"id":13,"text":"( R-ME )","depth":13},{"id":14,"text":"delivered her speech","depth":13},{"id":15,"text":"explaining why she would vote to confirm Judge Kavanaugh to the Supreme Court ,","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"a good friend of mine called .","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"She strongly disagreed with the Senator ' s decision","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"but was impressed with Collins ' tone , scholarliness and how she respectfully spoke of her Democratic colleagues","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"who opposed her position .","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"Our conversation echoed the findings of a recent Axios poll .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"It found","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"that more than half of Americans have had conversations about the Kavanaugh confirmation battle at work ,","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"and almost three quarters of Americans , like myself , have been talking about it with friends and family .","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"Most significant and surprising , over three quarters of Americans say","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"their discussions about the Supreme Court appointee have been civil .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"These poll results are in stark contrast to an annual poll tracking discourse in the United States ,","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"where 93 percent of Americans think","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"the U.S. has a civility problem .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"The percentage of Americans","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"viewing the opposite party unfavorably","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"has doubled in the last two decades ,","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"and 86 percent of Americans say","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"conflicts between Democrats and Republicans are strong or very strong .","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"In the Virginia Senate race , a Republican challenger pledged \" the most vicious , ruthless campaign \"","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"to unseat the Democrat incumbent","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"and in a series of exchanges , implied","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"without evidence ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"that his opponent committed sexual assault .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"A Democratic representative from California , warned members of Donald Trump ' s Cabinet to be prepared for an onslaught of heckling and public shaming","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"if they continue to support the president ' s policy on undocumented immigrants .","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"Notables from across the political spectrum are sounding the alarm ,","depth":4},{"id":42,"text":"warning us of the perils of our current path .","depth":4},{"id":43,"text":"Michelle Obama","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"Michelle LeVaughn Robinson","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"Obama","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"ichelle Obama praises Meghan Markle as 'an inspiration '","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"illary , Chelsea Clinton to appear on 'The View '","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"o talk new book , impeachment","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"dvocates find success in 'housing first '","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"o combat veteran homelessness","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"ORE said in a recent speech at a voter registration rally in Las Vegas","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"he is `` sick of the nastiness of our politics. \"","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"enator Jeff Flake","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"effrey","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"Jeff )","depth":15},{"id":56,"text":"ane FlakeRepublicans show signs of discomfort in defense of Trump","depth":15},{"id":57,"text":"indy McCain :","depth":15},{"id":58,"text":"can see Arizona 'going Democrat ' in 2020","depth":15},{"id":59,"text":"lake donates to Democratic sheriff","depth":15},{"id":60,"text":"eing challenged by Arpaio in Arizona","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"ORE","depth":15},{"id":62,"text":"R-AZ )","depth":15},{"id":63,"text":"uring the Kavanaugh hearings expressed","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"ow tribalism is ruining us ,","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"oing so far as to say","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"hat \" it is tearing our country apart . \"","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"t is evident :","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"ur civility problem is increasingly viewed as a serious threat to our nation .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"e need to shift our default model for public discourse","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"rom immediately employing fact-light , talking-point-based and anger-laced argument","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"o willingly seeking , and finding , common ground with the other side .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"o be sure , individuals with strong convictions should not be expected to compromise their values for the sake of civility .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"ut in today ' s bitterly divided political climate , finding common ground is paramount","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"o reducing toxic polarization","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"nd evoking civil dialogue .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"lected officials leverage and reflect the mindset of those","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"ho elect them .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"e as citizens can drive this change","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"y changing our mindset .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"ere ' s how .","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"ccept the fundamental truth","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"hat including more than one view contributes to a stronger position and a better , more effective solution .","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"e open-minded to facts","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"hat might conflict with our narrative ,","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"isten to others","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"ithout rushing to judgement","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"nd seek to understand why those","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"e disagree with","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"old the views","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"hey do .","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"ith midterm elections rapidly approaching ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"ast ballots for candidates with strong track records","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"f working with those with different political views .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"egardless of their party ,","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"hoose candidates","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"ho speak out against the speech and policies","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"esigned to divide us .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"e need to support organizations","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"orking to remove the threat .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"he blatant disregard for civility and a desire","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"o find a solution","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"ed to the creation of Common Ground Committee","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"CGC ) ,","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"hich inspires action on polarizing issues","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"y bringing prominent leaders with opposing views together in public forums","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"o find common ground .","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"fter the \" Unite the Right \" rally in Charlottesville , Virginia , Donna Brazile","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"former interim DNC chairwoman )","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"nd Michael Steele","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"former RNC chairman )","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"articipated in a CGC public forum","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"o discuss government ' s role","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"n bridging racial divides .","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"razile and Steele engaged with respect and a sense of conviction","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"hat we can all move beyond deep , destructive tribalism .","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"hey disagreed on the use of racial profiling and affirmative action","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"ut found common ground on the need","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"or police to live in the communities","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"hey serve ,","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"lection funding transparency","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"nd that voting districts should be drawn by citizens ' commissions , not politicians .","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"hey agreed","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"merica is a government of the people","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"nd encouraged the audience to get involved ,","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"o campaign ,","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"rite letters","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"nd run for office","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"not so much for President or State Representative ,","depth":15},{"id":129,"text":"ut for the School Board , the Finance Board , any place","depth":16},{"id":130,"text":"here the local community needs help .","depth":16},{"id":131,"text":"here is a growing movement for civil discourse ,","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"inding common ground","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"nd focusing on solutions rather than arguments .","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"iving Room Conversations and Better Angels cultivate positive , constructive conversations within our divided society .","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"he Bridge Alliance is a consortium of more than 90 civic action organizations","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"orking individually and together","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"o transform the political terrain .","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"hey stress listening , accepting nuances , putting country before self-interest and asking Americans with varying political beliefs and backgrounds to do the same .","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"e are in this together .","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"f enough of us can demonstrate the value and power of civil discourse ,","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"e can shift the cultural norm","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"rom winning at all costs","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"o finding common ground","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"henever possible .","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"e ' ll still see our leaders engaged in vigorous debate .","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"ut we ' ll also see them make progress quicker and more frequently on the issues","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"hat matter .","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"ruce Bond , a 30-year veteran of the information technology industry , is co-founder of the Common Ground Committee , a citizen-led initiative","depth":3},{"id":149,"text":"ocused on demonstrating productive public discourse .","depth":3},{"id":150,"text":"he nonprofit ' s next public forums will seek common ground on gun control , immigration and the press .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":301,"left":298,"right":300,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":298,"left":191,"right":297,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":191,"left":159,"right":190,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":156,"right":158,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":153,"right":155,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":153,"left":0,"right":152,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":154,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":154,"left":3,"right":